text: Kalvola is a former municipality in Kanta-Häme, Finland. In 2003, the municipality had a population of 3,449. Neighbouring municipalities were Hattula, Kylmäkoski, Tammela, Toijala, Urjala and Valkeakoski. It was merged with Hämeenlinna in 2009. == Other websites == * Official website Category:Former municipalities of Finland
